<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-06-05T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-06-05T14:00:00-05:00" n="549" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.51/1499a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hood</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-05T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 5,
                                        1922—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>18. Joint Resolution to authorize $5,000,000 loan to Liberia reported
                            favorably to Senate May 31st by Senate Finance Committee. It is hoped
                            Senate will take prompt action on Resolution. Inform Liberian
                            Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>